# CodeAlpha Hangman Game (Python)

This project is part of the **CodeAlpha Python Programming Internship**.  
It is a console-based Hangman game implemented using core Python concepts, with a small unique enhancement.

---

## üéØ Project Objective
To build a simple text-based Hangman game where the player guesses a hidden word one letter at a time within a limited number of incorrect attempts.

---

## ‚ú® Features
- Random word selection from a predefined list
- Player guesses one letter at a time
- Maximum of **6 incorrect guesses**
- Displays guessed and remaining letters
- **Smart Hint Feature**:
  - Automatically reveals one correct letter after **3 wrong guesses**
- Console-based interaction (no graphics)

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Concepts Used
- Python fundamentals
- `random` module
- Loops (`while`)
- Conditional statements (`if-else`)
- Strings and lists
- Sets for tracking guesses
- User input/output

---

## ‚ñ∂Ô∏è How to Run the Game

